  <h3>TL;DR, Cleartax for Indian filers and CAs</h3>
  <p>The default AI tax platform for India in 2026. Free ITR filing for most salaried users, paid tiers for capital gains and business income, dedicated CA suite for bulk GST and TDS. The AI is most useful in GST 2A/2B reconciliation, ITR auto-fill from AIS and Form 26AS, and the new GenAI tax chat. Indian payment native, GST invoice automatic.</p>
  <a href="https://cleartax.in" class="cta-button">Visit Cleartax</a>
</div>

<p>If you have filed an Indian ITR in the last five years, you have probably used Cleartax (formerly ClearTax / Defmacro) at least once. What most users do not realise is that the platform has quietly been adding genuine AI to its workflow, not as marketing copy but as workflow-changing features for GST reconciliation, ITR auto-population, and tax research.</p>

<p>This review covers the parts of Cleartax that actually benefit from AI in 2026, separately for individual filers, freelancers, businesses, and CAs.</p>

<h2>Where Cleartax's AI genuinely saves Indian users time</h2>

<h3>GST 2A/2B reconciliation</h3>
<p>The bulk of CA-firm GST work is matching purchase invoices to what suppliers have filed in GSTR-1, surfaced as your GSTR-2A/2B. Cleartax's AI auto-matches by GSTIN, invoice number, date, and amount; flags mismatches; suggests resolutions. What used to take a junior accountant a week now takes hours.</p>

<h3>ITR auto-population from AIS, TIS, Form 26AS, Form 16</h3>
<p>Cleartax pulls your annual information statement, tax information summary, Form 26AS, and Form 16 data, then reconciles them against your draft ITR. AI flags the deltas that need attention. For a salaried filer this turns "what numbers go where" into a one-pass review.</p>

<h3>GenAI tax chat for Indian queries</h3>
<p>"Can I claim HRA and home loan interest in the same year?" Asked of ChatGPT, you get a confident but partially wrong answer about American tax. Asked of Cleartax's tax chat, you get an answer grounded in the Income Tax Act with specific Sections cited. Indian tax specificity is the whole point.</p>

<h3>TDS reconciliation and notice response</h3>
<p>For Indian businesses, TDS reconciliation between Form 26Q, 24Q, and your books is a perennial source of notices. Cleartax's tools help match deductee data, flag short deductions, and draft preliminary notice responses.</p>

