<h2>Best Indian use cases</h2>

<h3>Salaried filers (₹0 use case)</h3>
<p>If your income is Form 16 + savings interest + maybe one capital gain, Cleartax free is enough. No CA needed unless you have complexity. Auto-population from AIS and 26AS gets you 90% of the way to filed in 15 minutes.</p>

<h3>Indian freelancers and consultants</h3>
<p>Quarterly advance tax estimation, ITR filing under presumptive (Section 44ADA) or regular books, GST registration and filing if you cross the threshold, and TDS by clients reconciled in one place. Cleartax's freelancer workflow is the cleanest in the market.</p>

<h3>D2C and SME businesses</h3>
<p>GST 2A/2B reconciliation, e-invoicing, e-way bills, TDS, audit support. Most modern Indian D2C ops have Cleartax as the tax-stack layer above their accounting system (Tally, Zoho Books, Razorpay).</p>

<h3>CA firms (this is the highest-leverage use case)</h3>
<p>The Cleartax for Professionals suite has become the operating system for many mid-size Indian CA firms doing 100+ GST filings a month. The AI reconciliation and notice-response drafting genuinely change capacity-per-CA economics.</p>

<h2>Where Cleartax is not the right tool</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Highly complex personal returns</strong>, HNI estate planning, multi-jurisdiction tax, complex trusts. You still want a senior CA, with Cleartax as the filing rails.</li>
  <li><strong>Specialised audit and assurance work</strong>, Cleartax is filing-focused, not audit-software focused. Caseware, MyAuditor, or Eximius remain audit-side defaults.</li>
  <li><strong>Cross-border ops</strong>, US ITIN filings, UK Self Assessment, etc. Cleartax is Indian tax law.</li>
  <li><strong>You want generative drafting for non-tax purposes</strong>, This is a tax platform, not a general-purpose AI.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Indian alternatives</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>TaxBuddy, Quicko, MyITReturn</strong>, Other Indian ITR-filing platforms, smaller scale, decent for salaried filers.</li>
  <li><strong>Zoho Books / Tally + manual filing</strong>, Accounting-first stacks, fine for small businesses willing to file manually.</li>
  <li><strong>Direct portal filing (incometax.gov.in)</strong>, Free, possible, painful for anything beyond the simplest cases.</li>
  <li><strong>Big 4 firms</strong>, For enterprise; not comparable to Cleartax for SME or individual workflow.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Indian-specific FAQs</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Does Cleartax actually use AI or is it just branding?</h3>
  <p>Genuine AI is used in three places: GST reconciliation (matching invoices to GSTR-2A/2B with automatic exception flagging), ITR drafting (auto-fills from Form 16, 26AS, AIS), and the new GenAI chat that answers Indian tax questions grounded in the live tax code. The rest of the platform is rules-based automation built on top of an enormous Indian tax-knowledge base.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Can a salaried Indian filer use Cleartax free?</h3>
  <p>Yes. Most salaried filers with Form 16 income can file ITR for free. Capital gains, business income, foreign income, and complex returns push you to paid tiers, which still cost less than a typical CA fee.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Is Cleartax usable by CAs for their client work?</h3>
  <p>Yes. The CA tier (Cleartax for Professionals / GST suite) is the workflow most Indian CA firms now use for bulk GST and TDS filing. The AI features save the most time on reconciliation and notice response drafting.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Does Cleartax accept UPI?</h3>
  <p>Yes, fully. Indian payment is native, GST invoice automatic, subscription deductible as a business expense.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>What about data privacy with my income data?</h3>
  <p>Cleartax holds RBI and IRDAI registrations for related fintech products and follows Indian data protection norms. For high-sensitivity work (HNIs, complex structures), most CAs still keep working papers in their own systems and use Cleartax as the filing layer.</p>
</div>

<h2>Final verdict</h2>

<p>For Indian individuals, freelancers, SMEs, and CAs, Cleartax is the default AI-augmented tax platform in 2026. Free for most salaried filers. Affordable paid tiers for everyone else. The AI features in GST reconciliation, ITR auto-population, and tax-specific chat are not marketing fluff; they save real hours.</p>

<p>For Indian CAs specifically, the Professionals suite has become difficult to compete with on workflow.</p>

